very interesting.

00:18:46.530 --> 00:18:48.931 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: What is
not-- What is it not?

00:18:48.931 --> 00:18:50.680 align:middle line:84%
You know, if we don't
know exactly what it

00:18:50.680 --> 00:18:52.077 align:middle line:90%
is, what is it not?

00:18:52.077 --> 00:18:53.660 align:middle line:84%
>>CHABOT: That's a
very good question.

00:18:53.660 --> 00:18:56.600 align:middle line:84%
And the first thing when
I meet clients is just

00:18:56.600 --> 00:18:59.640 align:middle line:84%
to clarify what is
hypnosis, what it's not,

00:18:59.640 --> 00:19:01.180 align:middle line:84%
and what do you
need for it to work?

00:19:01.180 --> 00:19:03.090 align:middle line:84%
Like, what do you
need to understand?

00:19:03.090 --> 00:19:05.700 align:middle line:84%
In hypnosis, you don't
lose consciousness.

00:19:05.700 --> 00:19:06.200 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:19:06.200 --> 00:19:07.116 align:middle line:90%
That's very important.

00:19:07.116 --> 00:19:10.340 align:middle line:84%
Some people-- they think
because of stage hypnosis,

00:19:10.340 --> 00:19:14.980 align:middle line:84%
because of movies they see
people sometimes waking

00:19:14.980 --> 00:19:17.190 align:middle line:84%
up and saying, oh my
god, what's happening?

00:19:17.190 --> 00:19:19.760 align:middle line:84%
That's because there's amnesia
happening at the moment.

00:19:19.760 --> 00:19:22.370 align:middle line:84%
But when you interview
someone on stage

00:19:22.370 --> 00:19:25.650 align:middle line:84%
and you ask them, so how was
it for you to be like this?

00:19:25.650 --> 00:19:28.280 align:middle line:84%
And most people say, like,
I felt really normal.

00:19:28.280 --> 00:19:31.220 align:middle line:84%
But there was just
something stronger

00:19:31.220 --> 00:19:33.300 align:middle line:90%
making me do it in some ways.

00:19:33.300 --> 00:19:33.800 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:19:33.800 --> 00:19:36.210 align:middle line:84%
And when I do street
hypnosis, I have

00:19:36.210 --> 00:19:37.960 align:middle line:84%
a lot of fun doing
this sometimes

00:19:37.960 --> 00:19:39.940 align:middle line:84%
because I'm going
to take someone--

00:19:39.940 --> 00:19:42.850 align:middle line:84%
even a skeptical person--
I'm going to do something

00:19:42.850 --> 00:19:45.320 align:middle line:84%
very quickly, rapid
induction, eyes open, wide

00:19:45.320 --> 00:19:47.210 align:middle line:84%
awake, OK, and they're
with their friends.

00:19:47.210 --> 00:19:49.500 align:middle line:84%
And then I say,
OK, now honestly.

00:19:49.500 --> 00:19:52.220 align:middle line:84%
Do you believe
you're hypnotised?

00:19:52.220 --> 00:19:56.060 align:middle line:84%
And 80% of the time people
look a bit shy or embarrassed.

00:19:56.060 --> 00:19:57.280 align:middle line:90%
Well, no, I don't think so.

00:19:57.280 --> 00:19:59.095 align:middle line:90%
OK, now try to move your feet.

00:19:59.095 --> 00:19:59.720 align:middle line:90%
And they can't.

00:19:59.720 --> 00:20:02.405 align:middle line:84%
I say like, sincerely,
you're not trying to fake it

00:20:02.405 --> 00:20:04.772 align:middle line:90%
or to please me or to play.

00:20:04.772 --> 00:20:05.730 align:middle line:90%
Can you move your feet?

00:20:05.730 --> 00:20:06.370 align:middle line:90%
They can't.

00:20:06.370 --> 00:20:07.340 align:middle line:90%
And do you feel hypnotised?

00:20:07.340 --> 00:20:07.839 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:20:07.839 --> 00:20:08.640 align:middle line:90%
Why can't you?

00:20:08.640 --> 00:20:10.070 align:middle line:90%
They say I don't know.

00:20:10.070 --> 00:20:13.520 align:middle line:84%
So it's a-- I would say it's an
unconscious change of reality.

00:20:13.520 --> 00:20:16.525 align:middle line:84%
And that's why, like, it's
interesting with Anthony

00:20:16.525 --> 00:20:21.660 align:middle line:84%
Jacquin and Kevin Sheldrake
who did some research

00:20:21.660 --> 00:20:24.650 align:middle line:84%
and they came up with
the automatic imagination

00:20:24.650 --> 00:20:28.210 align:middle line:84%
model, which is basically
about understanding

00:20:28.210 --> 00:20:32.410 align:middle line:84%
that, in hypnosis, your
unconscious is imagining things

00:20:32.410 --> 00:20:33.270 align:middle line:90%
automatically.

00:20:33.270 --> 00:20:33.770 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:20:33.770 --> 00:20:38.160 align:middle line:84%
So if I say you cannot stand up,
even if consciously you think

00:20:38.160 --> 00:20:40.670 align:middle line:84%
if you can't, there's a part
of you imagining that you

00:20:40.670 --> 00:20:44.180 align:middle line:84%
can't and this part has more
strength than the conscious

00:20:44.180 --> 00:20:48.840 align:middle line:84%
part because the unconscious
is much more powerful than

00:20:48.840 --> 00:20:49.640 align:middle line:90%
the conscious mind.

00:20:49.640 --> 00:20:51.181 align:middle line:84%
The imagination is
much more powerful

00:20:51.181 --> 00:20:52.520 align:middle line:90%
than the conscious mind.

00:20:52.520 --> 00:20:53.910 align:middle line:90%
So that's one thing.

00:20:53.910 --> 00:20:55.970 align:middle line:90%
You don't lose consciousness.

00:20:55.970 --> 00:20:59.640 align:middle line:84%
You're going to
remember what happens.

00:20:59.640 --> 00:21:02.205 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes people
forget some parts.

00:21:02.205 --> 00:21:03.080 align:middle line:90%
Sometimes it happens.

00:21:03.080 --> 00:21:05.230 align:middle line:84%
But I record everything,
especially when

00:21:05.230 --> 00:21:09.330 align:middle line:84%
we do spiritual past lives
so that they remember.

00:21:09.330 --> 00:21:11.440 align:middle line:84%
When we do hypnotherapy,
it's not necessarily

00:21:11.440 --> 00:21:14.440 align:middle line:84%
that we remember everything
because we want the unconscious

00:21:14.440 --> 00:21:18.680 align:middle line:84%
mind just to take it
in and organize it.

00:21:18.680 --> 00:21:20.250 align:middle line:90%
So there's this misconception.

00:21:20.250 --> 00:21:23.570 align:middle line:90%


00:21:23.570 --> 00:21:26.880 align:middle line:84%
Basically, yeah, I would say
that these are the main--

00:21:26.880 --> 00:21:28.620 align:middle line:84%
or that you lose
control that they

00:21:28.620 --> 00:21:30.360 align:middle line:84%
can make you do
anything you want.

00:21:30.360 --> 00:21:31.776 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Where
you're manipulated.

00:21:31.776 --> 00:21:32.850 align:middle line:90%
>>CHABOT: Yeah, exactly.

00:21:32.850 --> 00:21:34.140 align:middle line:90%
And I say, yes, it's true.

00:21:34.140 --> 00:21:35.015 align:middle line:90%
No, I'm just kidding.

00:21:35.015 --> 00:21:36.124 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:21:36.124 --> 00:21:37.290 align:middle line:90%
>>LILOU: Give me your money.

00:21:37.290 --> 00:21:37.685 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:21:37.685 --> 00:21:39.518 align:middle line:84%
>>CHABOT: But I tell
people-- I say, listen.

00:21:39.518 --> 00:21:43.500 align:middle line:84%
If it was true, all the
thieves would master hypnosis.

00:21:43.500 --> 00:21:45.430 align:middle line:84%
We would see this every
day in the newspaper.

00:21:45.430 --> 00:21:47.870 align:middle line:84%
Like, another one got
hypnotised to go--

00:21:47.870 --> 00:21:49.790 align:middle line:84%
there's a part of
us that protects us.

00:21:49.790 --> 00:21:50.560 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:21:50.560 --> 00:21:52.920 align:middle line:84%
And when people say, well,
what about stage hypnosis?

00:21:52.920 --> 00:21:54.290 align:middle line:90%
What about these people?

00:21:54.290 --> 00:21:55.400 align:middle line:90%
First, they're volunteers.

00:21:55.400 --> 00:21:56.550 align:middle line:90%
They're not actors.

00:21:56.550 --> 00:21:59.270 align:middle line:84%
When people say, oh,
they were actors,

00:21:59.270 --> 00:22:02.905 align:middle line:84%
there's nothing worse for
a hypnotherapist-- no,

00:22:02.905 --> 00:22:06.850 align:middle line:84%
a stage hypnotist to have actors
because people are bad actors.

00:22:06.850 --> 00:22:10.200 align:middle line:84%
It's much better to have three
good subjects than 10 people

00:22:10.200 --> 00:22:12.450 align:middle line:84%
with seven trying to please
their friend or please you

00:22:12.450 --> 00:22:12.949 align:middle line:90%
or whatever.

00:22:12.949 --> 00:22:15.225 align:middle line:84%
So some people, they don't
even have a bad intention.

00:22:15.225 --> 00:22:17.960 align:middle line:84%
Like, they're not hypnotised
and the hypnotherapist--

00:22:17.960 --> 00:22:21.120 align:middle line:84%
the hypnotist has to spot
them and thank you very much

00:22:21.120 --> 00:22:22.130 align:middle line:90%
to keep the people.

00:22:22.130 --> 00:22:23.560 align:middle line:90%
So they're real.

00:22:23.560 --> 00:22:24.760 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:22:24.760 --> 00:22:25.890 align:middle line:90%
And they're not acting.

00:22:25.890 --> 00:22:28.080 align:middle line:84%
But they're volunteers
to go there.

00:22:28.080 --> 00:22:29.350 align:middle line:90%
They know they're safe.

00:22:29.350 --> 00:22:31.262 align:middle line:84%
They know they're gonna--
They've heard that

00:22:31.262 --> 00:22:33.220 align:middle line:84%
they're probably going
to do some things funny,

00:22:33.220 --> 00:22:34.649 align:middle line:90%
so they're fine with it.

00:22:34.649 --> 00:22:36.190 align:middle line:84%
But if you hypnotize
someone and say,

00:22:36.190 --> 00:22:39.660 align:middle line:84%
OK, now give me your
money [BUZZER SOUND].

00:22:39.660 --> 00:22:41.994 align:middle line:84%
Like there's a little red
alarm that's going to come up.

00:22:41.994 --> 00:22:44.076 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Because it's like
we can hear everything.

00:22:44.076 --> 00:22:45.860 align:middle line:84%
>>CHABOT: You can
hear everything, yeah.

00:22:45.860 --> 00:22:47.670 align:middle line:84%
And even like, it's
really funny, Lilou.

00:22:47.670 --> 00:22:49.580 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes when I
give suggestions, OK,

00:22:49.580 --> 00:22:51.372 align:middle line:84%
next time your eyes
are going to open,

00:22:51.372 --> 00:22:53.580 align:middle line:84%
it's going to be impossible
for you to say your name.

00:22:53.580 --> 00:22:55.627 align:middle line:84%
The more you're going
to try to say your name,

00:22:55.627 --> 00:22:56.960 align:middle line:90%
the less it's going to come out.

00:22:56.960 --> 00:22:57.970 align:middle line:90%
It's going to be really funny.

00:22:57.970 --> 00:22:59.480 align:middle line:84%
And when I say
this, I see people

00:22:59.480 --> 00:23:01.310 align:middle line:90%
smiling like, yeah right.

00:23:01.310 --> 00:23:02.620 align:middle line:90%
OK? [SNAP] Eyes open.

00:23:02.620 --> 00:23:03.350 align:middle line:90%
Wide awake.

00:23:03.350 --> 00:23:04.200 align:middle line:90%
So what's your name?

00:23:04.200 --> 00:23:07.200 align:middle line:90%
And people go like-- OK?

00:23:07.200 --> 00:23:10.700 align:middle line:84%
So even if you hear
everything, but you still

00:23:10.700 --> 00:23:13.020 align:middle line:90%
have to want it to happen.

00:23:13.020 --> 00:23:16.010 align:middle line:84%
As I tell people when I
brief them before, I say,

00:23:16.010 --> 00:23:20.830 align:middle line:84%
you have to want it to happen,
to be open for it to happen,

00:23:20.830 --> 00:23:25.370 align:middle line:84%
but when I ask you
to try something,

00:23:25.370 --> 00:23:27.826 align:middle line:84%
I want you to honestly try,
especially when I do research

00:23:27.826 --> 00:23:29.200 align:middle line:84%
because I don't
want people fake.

00:23:29.200 --> 00:23:29.950 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:23:29.950 --> 00:23:32.330 align:middle line:84%
So they have to have on one
side, they want it to work.

00:23:32.330 --> 00:23:33.420 align:middle line:90%
They're open.

00:23:33.420 --> 00:23:36.210 align:middle line:84%
But on the other side, when I
ask them to test-- for example,

00:23:36.210 --> 00:23:39.470 align:middle line:84%
try to say your name or stand
up-- I want them to really try,

00:23:39.470 --> 00:23:41.500 align:middle line:90%
not to fake it.

00:23:41.500 --> 00:23:44.127 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Why does it
not work on some people?

00:23:44.127 --> 00:23:45.710 align:middle line:84%
>>CHABOT: That's a
very good question.

00:23:45.710 --> 00:23:49.000 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of--
there's different factors.

00:23:49.000 --> 00:23:51.710 align:middle line:84%
Some people-- I mean,
trust is important.

00:23:51.710 --> 00:23:55.640 align:middle line:84%
To have a feeling of-- if the
person is afraid, for example.

00:23:55.640 --> 00:23:57.020 align:middle line:90%
If they have misconception.

00:23:57.020 --> 00:23:59.229 align:middle line:90%
For example, some people--

00:23:59.229 --> 00:24:01.520 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Because they could
be afraid to be hypnotized.

00:24:01.520 --> 00:24:03.270 align:middle line:84%
That could be a first
fear right there.

00:24:03.270 --> 00:24:04.990 align:middle line:90%
>>CHABOT: Yeah, exactly.

00:24:04.990 --> 00:24:08.330 align:middle line:84%
That's why the job
of a hypnotherapist

00:24:08.330 --> 00:24:11.950 align:middle line:84%
is just to clarify all the
fears at the beginning.

00:24:11.950 --> 00:24:14.600 align:middle line:84%
And you explain it and then you
ask them do you have any fears?

00:24:14.600 --> 00:24:15.860 align:middle line:90%
Do you have anything?

00:24:15.860 --> 00:24:18.509 align:middle line:84%
Some people, for example,
I would clarify anything,

00:24:18.509 --> 00:24:20.300 align:middle line:84%
at the end I'll say,
OK, now are you ready?

00:24:20.300 --> 00:24:22.150 align:middle line:90%
And they say, yeah.

00:24:22.150 --> 00:24:25.100 align:middle line:84%
I said, I kind of feel
that there's something.

00:24:25.100 --> 00:24:29.350 align:middle line:84%
So, my aunt told me, like,
it's related with the devil.

00:24:29.350 --> 00:24:32.240 align:middle line:84%
And I say, well, because
in religion there's stuff

00:24:32.240 --> 00:24:33.980 align:middle line:84%
like-- of course,
it's not true--

00:24:33.980 --> 00:24:38.640 align:middle line:84%
but it's been like-- hypnosis--
religion didn't like it.

00:24:38.640 --> 00:24:40.320 align:middle line:90%
So you have to clarify this.

00:24:40.320 --> 00:24:40.930 align:middle line:90%
It's fine.

00:24:40.930 --> 00:24:41.804 align:middle line:90%
They're totally safe.

00:24:41.804 --> 00:24:43.190 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:24:43.190 --> 00:24:45.150 align:middle line:90%
So there's these fears.

00:24:45.150 --> 00:24:46.926 align:middle line:84%
And some people,
sometimes they say, like,

00:24:46.926 --> 00:24:48.300 align:middle line:84%
they're afraid
that they're going

00:24:48.300 --> 00:24:50.660 align:middle line:84%
to say things that
they don't want.

00:24:50.660 --> 00:24:52.700 align:middle line:84%
You're in control
of what you share.

00:24:52.700 --> 00:24:53.390 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:24:53.390 --> 00:24:57.700 align:middle line:84%
Unless you give the suggestion,
like, in this direction.

00:24:57.700 --> 00:25:00.639 align:middle line:84%
But the way we work,
you just-- I ask people,

00:25:00.639 --> 00:25:02.055 align:middle line:84%
you're going to
be in a state were

00:25:02.055 --> 00:25:04.013 align:middle line:84%
you're going to have
access to more information

00:25:04.013 --> 00:25:05.060 align:middle line:90%
that you normally have.

00:25:05.060 --> 00:25:08.340 align:middle line:84%
But you always have the
freedom to share what you want.

00:25:08.340 --> 00:25:11.647 align:middle line:84%
So if you access something,
it's too personal, it's fine,

00:25:11.647 --> 00:25:12.480 align:middle line:90%
keep it to yourself.

00:25:12.480 --> 00:25:14.646 align:middle line:84%
The important thing is that
you have it to yourself.

00:25:14.646 --> 00:25:17.090 align:middle line:84%
But when I do past
life regression

00:25:17.090 --> 00:25:19.095 align:middle line:84%
and in between
lives, I ask people,

00:25:19.095 --> 00:25:21.430 align:middle line:84%
I say, like, I'm going to
ask you a lot of questions

00:25:21.430 --> 00:25:23.309 align:middle line:84%
so that we record it
so that later on you're

00:25:23.309 --> 00:25:24.350 align:middle line:90%
going to have it for you.

00:25:24.350 --> 00:25:26.489 align:middle line:84%
But if there's something
you want to keep,

00:25:26.489 --> 00:25:27.655 align:middle line:90%
that's totally fine for you.

00:25:27.655 --> 00:25:30.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Where is that
information stored,

00:25:30.790 --> 00:25:34.150 align:middle line:84%
because some people talk about
akashic records to past life.

00:25:34.150 --> 00:25:34.700 align:middle line:90%
Where is it?

00:25:34.700 --> 00:25:36.010 align:middle line:90%
Is it in a cloud?

00:25:36.010 --> 00:25:37.230 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:25:37.230 --> 00:25:41.340 align:middle line:84%
>>CHABOT: I can say like the
cloud version of internet

00:25:41.340 --> 00:25:42.040 align:middle line:90%
today?

00:25:42.040 --> 00:25:46.200 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, it's connected with
the akashic memories.

00:25:46.200 --> 00:25:50.130 align:middle line:84%
As we know now or
what the science seems

00:25:50.130 --> 00:25:52.610 align:middle line:84%
to tell us about memory,
especially with Dr. Charbonnet,

00:25:52.610 --> 00:25:55.615 align:middle line:84%
like what he does
when people, like,

00:25:55.615 --> 00:25:58.610 align:middle line:84%
they are supposed to
be dead and they're out

00:25:58.610 --> 00:25:59.850 align:middle line:90%
and they access information.

00:25:59.850 --> 00:26:02.420 align:middle line:84%
They see things so they
have-- and Mario Beauregard

00:26:02.420 --> 00:26:05.162 align:middle line:84%
talks about it, as well--
they have a sense of identity.

00:26:05.162 --> 00:26:05.870 align:middle line:90%
They have memory.

00:26:05.870 --> 00:26:07.590 align:middle line:90%
They have emotions.

00:26:07.590 --> 00:26:09.180 align:middle line:84%
And then when they
come back-- so

00:26:09.180 --> 00:26:11.756 align:middle line:84%
there was not one neuron that
was moving in their brain.

00:26:11.756 --> 00:26:12.880 align:middle line:90%
And they still have memory.

00:26:12.880 --> 00:26:14.770 align:middle line:84%
They still have this
sense of identity.

00:26:14.770 --> 00:26:17.690 align:middle line:84%
So it's as if a
part of you-- of us,

00:26:17.690 --> 00:26:21.790 align:middle line:84%
basically, is just a receiver
or access this information,

00:26:21.790 --> 00:26:24.250 align:middle line:90%
which is not in our brain.

00:26:24.250 --> 00:26:27.470 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Even for people
wanting to-- that are smoking

00:26:27.470 --> 00:26:29.290 align:middle line:90%
and they want to stop smoking?

00:26:29.290 --> 00:26:32.680 align:middle line:84%
That's also an information
that is outside

00:26:32.680 --> 00:26:36.320 align:middle line:84%
or could some be stored
in our body and others

00:26:36.320 --> 00:26:38.990 align:middle line:90%
out depending on the issue?

00:26:38.990 --> 00:26:42.590 align:middle line:84%
>>CHABOT: There's
nothing in the body.

00:26:42.590 --> 00:26:44.482 align:middle line:90%
It's as if there's a--

00:26:44.482 --> 00:26:46.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: It's important
to talk about it.

00:26:46.190 --> 00:26:46.690 align:middle line:90%
>>CHABOT: Yeah, yea, yeah.

00:26:46.690 --> 00:26:48.370 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: This is not
too clear for us.

00:26:48.370 --> 00:26:51.000 align:middle line:84%
>>CHABOT: Yeah, it's a
field of consciousness.

00:26:51.000 --> 00:26:52.900 align:middle line:84%
And when you're open
to spirituality,

00:26:52.900 --> 00:26:57.500 align:middle line:84%
you basically have this
framework that you want to use

00:26:57.500 --> 00:27:00.740 align:middle line:84%
people's-- let's call
them-- challenges.

00:27:00.740 --> 00:27:06.200 align:middle line:84%
Whether it's stop smoking or
anything that they have like--

00:27:06.200 --> 00:27:09.010 align:middle line:84%
I don't know, like
biting nails or whatever.

00:27:09.010 --> 00:27:09.840 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:27:09.840 --> 00:27:11.450 align:middle line:84%
So you could do
work just with that.

00:27:11.450 --> 00:27:14.180 align:middle line:84%
But I want to use
these challenges to act

00:27:14.180 --> 00:27:16.560 align:middle line:84%
as a springboard in
their spiritual life

00:27:16.560 --> 00:27:19.360 align:middle line:84%
so that the changes that
they're going to make

00:27:19.360 --> 00:27:23.340 align:middle line:84%
is going to be really
helpful in others' fears.

00:27:23.340 --> 00:27:25.230 align:middle line:84%
And that's a bit
where I would say

00:27:25.230 --> 00:27:28.600 align:middle line:84%
the way I do hypnotherapy will
differ from other kinds of more

00:27:28.600 --> 00:27:32.530 align:middle line:84%
classic kinds of hypnotherapy,
which they will say,

00:27:32.530 --> 00:27:34.650 align:middle line:84%
for example, OK, if
you're a good subject,

00:27:34.650 --> 00:27:35.700 align:middle line:90%
now you're a non-smoker.

00:27:35.700 --> 00:27:36.830 align:middle line:90%
You hate smoking.

00:27:36.830 --> 00:27:37.730 align:middle line:90%
Tasting smoke is bad.

00:27:37.730 --> 00:27:40.380 align:middle line:84%
You forgot you ever
smoked in your life, OK?

00:27:40.380 --> 00:27:43.750 align:middle line:84%
With a very good subject, this
could work and could maybe even

00:27:43.750 --> 00:27:45.470 align:middle line:90%
last a long time.

00:27:45.470 --> 00:27:49.450 align:middle line:84%
But from my point of view, my
perspective, every challenges

00:27:49.450 --> 00:27:52.140 align:middle line:84%
we should grow from
this experience.

00:27:52.140 --> 00:27:54.130 align:middle line:84%
So even when I do
hypnosis, I'm going

00:27:54.130 --> 00:27:56.790 align:middle line:84%
to ask the unconscious
mind to make it such

00:27:56.790 --> 00:27:59.920 align:middle line:84%
that it's going to be
easier to stop smoking

00:27:59.920 --> 00:28:04.030 align:middle line:84%
but the individual will
have to put in the effort

00:28:04.030 --> 00:28:06.890 align:middle line:84%
because when you put
effort, you feel proud.

00:28:06.890 --> 00:28:09.060 align:middle line:84%
You connect with
resources inside of you,

00:28:09.060 --> 00:28:11.840 align:middle line:84%
which are transferable to
other aspects of your life.

00:28:11.840 --> 00:28:15.390 align:middle line:84%
So we want to help it but
we don't-- it's not a way

00:28:15.390 --> 00:28:17.810 align:middle line:84%
of, like, programming
and deprogramming

00:28:17.810 --> 00:28:19.390 align:middle line:90%
and reprogramming.

00:28:19.390 --> 00:28:22.400 align:middle line:84%
It's just really to
help in an organic way

00:28:22.400 --> 00:28:25.120 align:middle line:84%
to connect with what's
important-- all the resources--

00:28:25.120 --> 00:28:27.440 align:middle line:84%
so that they make the change
and that they feel proud

00:28:27.440 --> 00:28:28.595 align:middle line:90%
about themselves.

00:28:28.595 --> 00:28:30.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: There's
still free will.

00:28:30.100 --> 00:28:36.080 align:middle line:84%
>>CHABOT: There is still free
will and they're responsible.

00:28:36.080 --> 00:28:40.000 align:middle line:84%
It's not like sometimes people
come and say, OK, talk to me.

00:28:40.000 --> 00:28:42.800 align:middle line:84%
You know, I want to get
rid of this problem.

00:28:42.800 --> 00:28:44.220 align:middle line:90%
Go do the job.

00:28:44.220 --> 00:28:45.340 align:middle line:90%
Go in my brain.

00:28:45.340 --> 00:28:47.270 align:middle line:84%
I don't care what
you do, just do it.

00:28:47.270 --> 00:28:47.960 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:28:47.960 --> 00:28:50.280 align:middle line:84%
And I don't work like
this because it's

00:28:50.280 --> 00:28:52.470 align:middle line:90%
a interactive process.

00:28:52.470 --> 00:28:53.970 align:middle line:90%
It's a dance.

00:28:53.970 --> 00:28:56.600 align:middle line:84%
And people have to be
involved in the process

00:28:56.600 --> 00:28:58.260 align:middle line:90%
and do the action plans.

00:28:58.260 --> 00:29:02.030 align:middle line:84%
Like, we do stuff and then
they have a spiritual practice

00:29:02.030 --> 00:29:04.670 align:middle line:84%
or they put in
action some things

00:29:04.670 --> 00:29:06.300 align:middle line:90%
to really integrate the change.

00:29:06.300 --> 00:29:08.480 align:middle line:84%
So it's a feedback--
like we say, OK,

00:29:08.480 --> 00:29:13.508 align:middle line:84%
how did it go-- to help
people be more complete.

00:29:13.508 --> 00:29:14.762 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, basically.

00:29:14.762 --> 00:29:16.500 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: What is
your personal story

00:29:16.500 --> 00:29:18.131 align:middle line:90%
that brought you to hypnosis?

00:29:18.131 --> 00:29:19.557 align:middle line:90%
>>CHABOT: Ah.

00:29:19.557 --> 00:29:20.390 align:middle line:90%
That's a long story.

00:29:20.390 --> 00:29:22.556 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: What is your growth
to spiritual awakening?

00:29:22.556 --> 00:29:24.346 align:middle line:90%
>>CHABOT: OK.

00:29:24.346 --> 00:29:28.264 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Have you always been
interested by these topics?

00:29:28.264 --> 00:29:29.680 align:middle line:84%
>>CHABOT: Actually,
when I was 16,

00:29:29.680 --> 00:29:32.290 align:middle line:90%
I had an out of body experience.

00:29:32.290 --> 00:29:35.800 align:middle line:84%
I was really interested
about-- well,

00:29:35.800 --> 00:29:38.830 align:middle line:84%
I had a friend who talked
to me about spiritual stuff.

00:29:38.830 --> 00:29:42.490 align:middle line:84%
Like, Ramtha was the first
book I read awhile ago.

00:29:42.490 --> 00:29:45.300 align:middle line:84%
And then "De Memoire
D'Essenien" from Daniel Meurois,

00:29:45.300 --> 00:29:48.780 align:middle line:90%
which is an amazing book.

00:29:48.780 --> 00:29:50.617 align:middle line:84%
So then I was doing
out of body experience.

00:29:50.617 --> 00:29:52.450 align:middle line:84%
I was like, oh my god,
I have to learn this.

00:29:52.450 --> 00:29:56.270 align:middle line:84%
I went to get a
book, and I studied,

00:29:56.270 --> 00:30:00.000 align:middle line:84%
I practiced a technique
during the whole day,

00:30:00.000 --> 00:30:01.610 align:middle line:90%
and it happened in the night.

00:30:01.610 --> 00:30:04.520 align:middle line:84%
So I actually left
my body and saw--

00:30:04.520 --> 00:30:07.930 align:middle line:84%
and which was really interesting
is that when I left my body,

00:30:07.930 --> 00:30:10.620 align:middle line:84%
I had the feeling-- usually
I would have been like,

00:30:10.620 --> 00:30:11.860 align:middle line:90%
oh my god, this is cool.

00:30:11.860 --> 00:30:13.150 align:middle line:90%
You know, you're 16 years old.

00:30:13.150 --> 00:30:17.510 align:middle line:84%
But I felt more like an
expansion of the mind

00:30:17.510 --> 00:30:20.200 align:middle line:84%
as I was more myself
outside than inside.

00:30:20.200 --> 00:30:23.560 align:middle line:84%
And I remember the thought was
like, huh, I'm aware of it now.

00:30:23.560 --> 00:30:25.110 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't like, oh, cool.

00:30:25.110 --> 00:30:29.220 align:middle line:84%
And then I went to the
kitchen, went through the door.

00:30:29.220 --> 00:30:30.890 align:middle line:84%
And it's really
different from a dream.

00:30:30.890 --> 00:30:32.580 align:middle line:84%
Like, when people
say, well, how do

00:30:32.580 --> 00:30:34.492 align:middle line:84%
you know it's not--
When you experience it,

00:30:34.492 --> 00:30:35.700 align:middle line:90%
it's like apples and oranges.

00:30:35.700 --> 00:30:36.290 align:middle line:90%
You know.

00:30:36.290 --> 00:30:38.000 align:middle line:90%
It's really clear.

00:30:38.000 --> 00:30:42.790 align:middle line:84%
And then at some point I was
rehearsing a visualization.

00:30:42.790 --> 00:30:44.940 align:middle line:84%
Basically, I didn't
drink all day.

00:30:44.940 --> 00:30:45.530 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:30:45.530 --> 00:30:48.090 align:middle line:84%
And I was visualizing
drinking water.

00:30:48.090 --> 00:30:50.660 align:middle line:84%
And when I drink water
to remember myself,

00:30:50.660 --> 00:30:53.780 align:middle line:84%
that I am to become aware
so that I'm out of the body

00:30:53.780 --> 00:30:55.830 align:middle line:84%
so that was like the
gist of the technique.

00:30:55.830 --> 00:30:58.790 align:middle line:84%
So it's as if like, by
default, I went in the kitchen,

00:30:58.790 --> 00:31:03.140 align:middle line:84%
I went to the glass of
water, but when I drank,

00:31:03.140 --> 00:31:06.300 align:middle line:84%
I got beamed up in some
kind of astral hospital

00:31:06.300 --> 00:31:09.615 align:middle line:90%
where I met beings.

00:31:09.615 --> 00:31:11.360 align:middle line:90%
>>LILOU: Who did you meet?

00:31:11.360 --> 00:31:13.740 align:middle line:84%
>>CHABOT: No, it was
just like light beings

00:31:13.740 --> 00:31:16.040 align:middle line:90%
or really wise beings.

00:31:16.040 --> 00:31:18.180 align:middle line:84%
And there was like
some kind of doctor

00:31:18.180 --> 00:31:21.099 align:middle line:84%
who-- I don't really
usually tell this.

00:31:21.099 --> 00:31:21.890 align:middle line:90%
Keep this a secret.

00:31:21.890 --> 00:31:23.506 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:31:23.506 --> 00:31:26.610 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: This is a great
community to share it with.

00:31:26.610 --> 00:31:29.680 align:middle line:84%
>>CHABOT: Yeah, and
what I remember was he

00:31:29.680 --> 00:31:33.149 align:middle line:84%
kind of had bigger
eyes in some ways.

00:31:33.149 --> 00:31:34.690 align:middle line:84%
But he was telling
me a lot of stuff.

00:31:34.690 --> 00:31:39.050 align:middle line:84%
And he was telling me stuff
about my mom would be sick.

00:31:39.050 --> 00:31:42.810 align:middle line:84%
And just a lot of stuff,
which was really interesting

00:31:42.810 --> 00:31:44.050 align:middle line:90%
because my mom wasn't sick.

00:31:44.050 --> 00:31:45.670 align:middle line:84%
And the next morning--
the ambulance.

00:31:45.670 --> 00:31:47.440 align:middle line:90%
We had to call the ambulance.

00:31:47.440 --> 00:31:48.745 align:middle line:90%
So there was a--

00:31:48.745 --> 00:31:50.610 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: So the timing
was pretty perfect.

00:31:50.610 --> 00:31:54.270 align:middle line:84%
That often happens with
those kind of paranormal

00:31:54.270 --> 00:31:57.350 align:middle line:84%
or whatever we call
it but anyway, you

00:31:57.350 --> 00:31:59.654 align:middle line:84%
know a different
kind of experience.

00:31:59.654 --> 00:32:01.320 align:middle line:84%
>>CHABOT: So that's
why, basically, it's

00:32:01.320 --> 00:32:03.990 align:middle line:84%
this experience that-- at
16 years old-- I understood,

00:32:03.990 --> 00:32:08.380 align:middle line:84%
which like for me today, I
don't remember the whole thing.

00:32:08.380 --> 00:32:11.360 align:middle line:84%
But it just opened
up inside of me

00:32:11.360 --> 00:32:14.840 align:middle line:84%
knowing that there's much
more out there than what

00:32:14.840 --> 00:32:17.920 align:middle line:90%
seems to be the case.

00:32:17.920 --> 00:32:19.405 align:middle line:90%
There's other dimensions.

00:32:19.405 --> 00:32:24.544 align:middle line:84%
Other ways of-- Other levels
of realities, basically.

00:32:24.544 --> 00:32:26.585 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: That's pretty
young to be aware of that.

00:32:26.585 --> 00:32:27.380 align:middle line:90%
>>CHABOT: Yeah.

00:32:27.380 --> 00:32:28.980 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: What did
you do with it then?

00:32:28.980 --> 00:32:31.940 align:middle line:84%
Did you start studying
or you curiosity was--

00:32:31.940 --> 00:32:34.080 align:middle line:84%
>>CHABOT: Well
actually, this kind of

00:32:34.080 --> 00:32:40.099 align:middle line:84%
triggered a really intense
desire to learn about humans.

00:32:40.099 --> 00:32:41.640 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Everything
about everything.

00:32:41.640 --> 00:32:45.110 align:middle line:84%
>>CHABOT: Yeah, but what
really interested me the most

00:32:45.110 --> 00:32:48.490 align:middle line:84%
and I did my thesis on this--
my master's degree thesis--

00:32:48.490 --> 00:32:49.870 align:middle line:90%
on interpersonal change.

00:32:49.870 --> 00:32:50.710 align:middle line:90%
How we change.

00:32:50.710 --> 00:32:54.610 align:middle line:84%
How human beings evolve
different paradigms of change.

00:32:54.610 --> 00:32:59.361 align:middle line:84%
And this is where when I did
literature [SPEAKING FRENCH]

00:32:59.361 --> 00:32:59.860 align:middle line:90%
literature?

00:32:59.860 --> 00:33:01.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LILOU: Mm, that's one that--

00:33:01.950 --> 00:33:04.070 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHING]

00:33:04.070 --> 00:33:04.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LILOU: A review!

