>>CHABOT: A review like
when you do research,

00:33:06.695 --> 00:33:08.380 align:middle line:84%
you just read a lot
of stuff, basically.

00:33:08.380 --> 00:33:09.670 align:middle line:90%
So in the literature.

00:33:09.670 --> 00:33:13.660 align:middle line:84%
And there were some, of course,
articles about hypnosis being

00:33:13.660 --> 00:33:15.940 align:middle line:84%
an interesting
modality to change.

00:33:15.940 --> 00:33:18.540 align:middle line:84%
And then-- like
very short story.

00:33:18.540 --> 00:33:21.040 align:middle line:84%
And then later on
after my master's, I

00:33:21.040 --> 00:33:23.580 align:middle line:84%
was in China for five years
doing corporate training,

00:33:23.580 --> 00:33:26.310 align:middle line:84%
teaching presentation skills,
confidence building skills,

00:33:26.310 --> 00:33:28.620 align:middle line:84%
and stuff like that,
communication skills.

00:33:28.620 --> 00:33:31.820 align:middle line:84%
And then I started
integrating in hypnosis.

00:33:31.820 --> 00:33:34.730 align:middle line:84%
But I hadn't had any
training, formal training.

00:33:34.730 --> 00:33:36.550 align:middle line:84%
So when I was in
Beijing, I decided

00:33:36.550 --> 00:33:39.570 align:middle line:84%
to do my first
training in California.

00:33:39.570 --> 00:33:42.570 align:middle line:84%
And this is where, even though
it was a normal hypnotherapy

00:33:42.570 --> 00:33:46.040 align:middle line:84%
training, the
teacher-- the trainer--

00:33:46.040 --> 00:33:48.800 align:middle line:84%
