How do you know it's not?

00:36:09.230 --> 00:36:12.640 align:middle line:84%
And I tell people, on one
level, the important thing

00:36:12.640 --> 00:36:15.070 align:middle line:84%
is that there's
a reason why this

00:36:15.070 --> 00:36:17.040 align:middle line:90%
happened and not something else.

00:36:17.040 --> 00:36:20.470 align:middle line:84%
And what's important is to
learn from it because even

00:36:20.470 --> 00:36:22.150 align:middle line:84%
if the mind just
created a metaphor

00:36:22.150 --> 00:36:26.320 align:middle line:84%
to help you release a fear or
do something that helps you

00:36:26.320 --> 00:36:28.260 align:middle line:90%
and you're better, who cares?

00:36:28.260 --> 00:36:28.760 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:36:28.760 --> 00:36:33.480 align:middle line:84%
But I did have some clients, of
course, that we went on Google

00:36:33.480 --> 00:36:38.540 align:middle line:84%
and checked out some information
and really interesting stuff.

00:36:38.540 --> 00:36:40.310 align:middle line:84%
Like, I mean, I
could talk about this

00:36:40.310 --> 00:36:44.320 align:middle line:84%
but it's real interesting
when you verify information

00:36:44.320 --> 00:36:45.620 align:middle line:90%
and the person is like, whoa.

00:36:45.620 --> 00:36:46.120 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:36:46.120 --> 00:36:48.020 align:middle line:84%
It's like stuff
like he was living

00:36:48.020 --> 00:36:49.694 align:middle line:90%
in a-- Just a quick example.

00:36:49.694 --> 00:36:50.360 align:middle line:90%
Do we have time?

00:36:50.360 --> 00:36:50.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LILOU: Mm hm.

00:36:50.780 --> 00:36:51.040 align:middle line:90%
>>CHABOT: Yeah?

00:36:51.040 --> 00:36:51.540 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:36:51.540 --> 00:36:58.205 align:middle line:84%
Quick example, this guy was
living in a village in France.

00:36:58.205 --> 00:37:04.200 align:middle line:84%
It was Chapelle-Glain which is
like 1,000 people or something.

00:37:04.200 --> 00:37:04.955 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:37:04.955 --> 00:37:06.830 align:middle line:84%
And it was really
interesting because the guy

00:37:06.830 --> 00:37:08.150 align:middle line:90%
before, he was really stressed.

00:37:08.150 --> 00:37:12.546 align:middle line:84%
He was like, I'm not afraid
of what I'm going to access.

00:37:12.546 --> 00:37:14.170 align:middle line:84%
It's I'm afraid it's
not going to work.

00:37:14.170 --> 00:37:15.840 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, everybody says that.

00:37:15.840 --> 00:37:16.380 align:middle line:90%
You're fine.

00:37:16.380 --> 00:37:17.540 align:middle line:84%
You know, just follow
the suggestions.

00:37:17.540 --> 00:37:18.687 align:middle line:90%
It's going to be good.

00:37:18.687 --> 00:37:20.270 align:middle line:84%
And the guy was a
really good subject.

00:37:20.270 --> 00:37:24.580 align:middle line:84%
And he was like in-- So all
the information, his wife, five

00:37:24.580 --> 00:37:28.160 align:middle line:84%
kids, everything was
coming really quickly.

00:37:28.160 --> 00:37:31.130 align:middle line:84%
And he was calling it
though Chapelle-Glain.

00:37:31.130 --> 00:37:34.217 align:middle line:84%
And then we found it
was Chapelle-Glain.

00:37:34.217 --> 00:37:36.050 align:middle line:84%
The church-- he looked
at the church and was

00:37:36.050 --> 00:37:38.290 align:middle line:84%
like, oh my god, this
is really familiar.

00:37:38.290 --> 00:37:42.830 align:middle line:84%
The next lifetime he was like
an American Indian person.

00:37:42.830 --> 00:37:44.660 align:middle line:84%
And I said what's the
name of the tribe?

00:37:44.660 --> 00:37:48.880 align:middle line:84%
He said, Swampy Cree,
which he never heard.

00:37:48.880 --> 00:37:51.520 align:middle line:84%
He said, but our tipis
are not like triangular.

00:37:51.520 --> 00:37:53.810 align:middle line:84%
They were a bit
like round shapes.

00:37:53.810 --> 00:37:59.150 align:middle line:84%
So afterwards we go on Google,
and we find Swampy Cree's.

00:37:59.150 --> 00:38:00.620 align:middle line:90%
And he was looking at it.

00:38:00.620 --> 00:38:05.440 align:middle line:84%
So when you verify stuff
like this, it's interesting.

00:38:05.440 --> 00:38:09.530 align:middle line:84%
But for me, the most
interesting is the healing

00:38:09.530 --> 00:38:13.895 align:middle line:84%
or the liberation that really
happens when we do this work.

00:38:13.895 --> 00:38:17.960 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Even on pains
or physical problems?

00:38:17.960 --> 00:38:19.270 align:middle line:90%
>>CHABOT: It happens sometimes.

00:38:19.270 --> 00:38:20.144 align:middle line:90%
It happens sometimes.

00:38:20.144 --> 00:38:22.310 align:middle line:84%
Like, we're never
going to advertise it

00:38:22.310 --> 00:38:23.610 align:middle line:90%
or we can't say that we heal.

00:38:23.610 --> 00:38:26.570 align:middle line:84%
It's just sometimes that
people are free, sometimes,

00:38:26.570 --> 00:38:28.610 align:middle line:90%
from problems.

00:38:28.610 --> 00:38:31.377 align:middle line:84%
But I would never
recommend that someone--

00:38:31.377 --> 00:38:32.710 align:middle line:90%
like, for me, it's a compliment.

00:38:32.710 --> 00:38:35.110 align:middle line:84%
Like if you have an illness,
you stay with your doctor,

00:38:35.110 --> 00:38:36.150 align:middle line:90%
you do this.

00:38:36.150 --> 00:38:37.770 align:middle line:84%
But you can do this
as a complement

00:38:37.770 --> 00:38:40.780 align:middle line:84%
to help you understand it
and change your view of it--

00:38:40.780 --> 00:38:42.520 align:middle line:90%
your understanding of it.

00:38:42.520 --> 00:38:44.210 align:middle line:84%
But sometimes, yeah,
I did have people

00:38:44.210 --> 00:38:49.220 align:middle line:84%
who had pain and then something
just-- like for example--

00:38:49.220 --> 00:38:50.930 align:middle line:90%
like a really big knee pain.

00:38:50.930 --> 00:38:51.530 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:38:51.530 --> 00:38:53.150 align:middle line:84%
And then I was like, with
the guides, sometimes

00:38:53.150 --> 00:38:54.149 align:middle line:90%
it's really interesting.

00:38:54.149 --> 00:38:56.900 align:middle line:84%
You just ask the guides, is
there something you can do?

00:38:56.900 --> 00:38:57.850 align:middle line:90%
And they say, sure.

00:38:57.850 --> 00:39:01.070 align:middle line:84%
And the guy said, OK, I just
feel this energy on my knee

00:39:01.070 --> 00:39:02.370 align:middle line:90%
and I see images.

00:39:02.370 --> 00:39:04.040 align:middle line:84%
And I was like, oh,
what kind of images?

00:39:04.040 --> 00:39:07.710 align:middle line:84%
He said there's images of money,
of this person, of that person,

00:39:07.710 --> 00:39:09.350 align:middle line:84%
like, and then we
can make clinks

00:39:09.350 --> 00:39:11.720 align:middle line:84%
like memories, cellular
memory or something.

00:39:11.720 --> 00:39:15.550 align:middle line:84%
And afterward, he was
moving like, whoa.

00:39:15.550 --> 00:39:19.390 align:middle line:84%
The pain is gone in some
way, so stuff happens.

00:39:19.390 --> 00:39:23.000 align:middle line:84%
Like, reality is really
more complex and beautiful,

00:39:23.000 --> 00:39:26.800 align:middle line:84%
and I would even dare to
say-- maybe not magical--

00:39:26.800 --> 00:39:29.570 align:middle line:84%
but in some way there's
really something that's

00:39:29.570 --> 00:39:32.270 align:middle line:84%
really fascinating
about all this.

00:39:32.270 --> 00:39:37.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Last little thing-- on
autohypnosis, self- hypnosis.

00:39:37.420 --> 00:39:39.380 align:middle line:90%
>>CHABOT: Yeah, self-hypnosis.

00:39:39.380 --> 00:39:40.740 align:middle line:90%
For me, I had an illness.

00:39:40.740 --> 00:39:42.390 align:middle line:84%
So I used self-hypnosis
to really--

00:39:42.390 --> 00:39:45.800 align:middle line:84%
it was supposed to
be incurable illness.

00:39:45.800 --> 00:39:46.830 align:middle line:90%
Scleroderma.

00:39:46.830 --> 00:39:51.880 align:middle line:84%
And I really used it,
basically,-- self-hypnosis--

00:39:51.880 --> 00:39:54.240 align:middle line:90%
to help get better basically.

00:39:54.240 --> 00:39:55.560 align:middle line:90%
So there's different ways.

00:39:55.560 --> 00:39:57.870 align:middle line:84%
You could go see a
hypnotherapist who

00:39:57.870 --> 00:40:02.700 align:middle line:84%
does a session with you and
then gives you a way to go back.

00:40:02.700 --> 00:40:04.170 align:middle line:84%
Or you can practice
it by yourself.

00:40:04.170 --> 00:40:06.370 align:middle line:84%
There's different books
or different things

00:40:06.370 --> 00:40:10.196 align:middle line:84%
you can say or do inside
of you to get in the state

00:40:10.196 --> 00:40:11.820 align:middle line:84%
and then you can do
some visualization,

00:40:11.820 --> 00:40:14.580 align:middle line:90%
which is extremely powerful.

00:40:14.580 --> 00:40:16.969 align:middle line:84%
Like, the neuro science
of visualization.

00:40:16.969 --> 00:40:19.260 align:middle line:84%
The brain doesn't make a
difference between what's real

00:40:19.260 --> 00:40:20.210 align:middle line:90%
and imagined.

00:40:20.210 --> 00:40:22.120 align:middle line:90%
So there's this aspect.

00:40:22.120 --> 00:40:23.860 align:middle line:90%
Or it can be affirmations.

00:40:23.860 --> 00:40:26.690 align:middle line:84%
There can be like, to
connect with the feeling,

00:40:26.690 --> 00:40:30.359 align:middle line:84%
I stress the emphasis on
really feeling and Bashar talks

00:40:30.359 --> 00:40:32.650 align:middle line:84%
about this really clearly,
which is really interesting.

00:40:32.650 --> 00:40:36.520 align:middle line:84%
He said, the visualization,
it doesn't really matter.

00:40:36.520 --> 00:40:39.810 align:middle line:84%
The visualization is
basically a pretext

00:40:39.810 --> 00:40:42.970 align:middle line:84%
to feel the emotion
of what it will

00:40:42.970 --> 00:40:45.400 align:middle line:84%
be like when you're
healed; when you're good.

00:40:45.400 --> 00:40:48.270 align:middle line:84%
And then your higher
self takes this feeling

00:40:48.270 --> 00:40:53.870 align:middle line:84%
and then finds ways to
manifest this in some ways.

00:40:53.870 --> 00:40:56.450 align:middle line:84%
But self-hypnosis is
really interesting.

00:40:56.450 --> 00:40:58.570 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people
I would recommend.

00:40:58.570 --> 00:41:03.070 align:middle line:84%
Even if you have an operation,
hypnosis before the operation

00:41:03.070 --> 00:41:04.570 align:middle line:84%
and afterwards to
help with healing.

00:41:04.570 --> 00:41:06.970 align:middle line:84%
I did stuff for
people close to me.

00:41:06.970 --> 00:41:09.050 align:middle line:90%
And MP3s.

00:41:09.050 --> 00:41:11.920 align:middle line:10%
MP3s is a really
good way to just

00:41:11.920 --> 00:41:15.470 align:middle line:10%
to learn to be guided
because the biggest

00:41:15.470 --> 00:41:18.660 align:middle line:10%
difficulty with
self-hypnosis is,

00:41:18.660 --> 00:41:21.620 align:middle line:10%
if you don't do it with
anything, it's possible.

00:41:21.620 --> 00:41:22.990 align:middle line:10%
You know, I've done it.

00:41:22.990 --> 00:41:25.660 align:middle line:10%
But it's just a part of
you has to guide yourself

00:41:25.660 --> 00:41:27.660 align:middle line:10%
and a part of you has
to have the experience.

00:41:27.660 --> 00:41:28.890 align:middle line:90%
You have to keep track.

00:41:28.890 --> 00:41:30.170 align:middle line:90%
OK, I'm doing this.

00:41:30.170 --> 00:41:32.480 align:middle line:84%
Whereas, if you have a
hypnotherapist or MP3, you

00:41:32.480 --> 00:41:34.050 align:middle line:84%
just-- you don't
have to guide it.

00:41:34.050 --> 00:41:35.025 align:middle line:90%
You just follow.

00:41:35.025 --> 00:41:35.960 align:middle line:90%
>>LILOU: Relax, sure.

00:41:35.960 --> 00:41:38.130 align:middle line:84%
>>CHABOT: You just relax,
follow suggestions.

00:41:38.130 --> 00:41:39.213 align:middle line:90%
That's all you have to do.

00:41:39.213 --> 00:41:40.570 align:middle line:90%
So it's all possible.

00:41:40.570 --> 00:41:42.606 align:middle line:90%
It's just different options.

00:41:42.606 --> 00:41:44.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LILOU: Last little
